ECS is seeking a Product Management Consultant to work in our Arlington, VA office.

ECS is seeking a Product Management Lead (Consulting & Execution) to support a diverse portfolio of federal client engagements and to facilitate product planning, execution, and delivery throughout the Product Lifecycle to ensure fulfillment of the product vision and maximize the customer experience. This position supports our National Security customer, in the delivery of Cybersecurity products and services. Duties include, but are not limited to managing scrum activities, client research, requirements gathering, project artifact creation, and project management of the engagement. A successful Product Manager will build relationships with his/her clients and manage the execution of daily, weekly, and monthly deliverables. This role will lead scrum activities and serve as the product management consultant.

Job Description:
• Own and guide the functional creation and evolution of products by developing against needs that are voiced directly by clients and their customers as well as proactively recommend functionality based on your expertise and industry/competitor trends;
• Manage several major initiatives defined by clients and drive execution and delivery across several multi-disciplinary teams
• Translating client feedback/requests into product ideas;
• Participate in discussions with clients, users, third-party vendors, data source providers, business SMEs and other parties as necessary to gather product requirements;
• Own and manage sprint pElanning
• Analyze usage statistics, other client reporting metrics and operating metrics. Based on the analysis, deliver recommendations to the client for product and process based on analysis;
• Liaise with the business owners to ensure the backlogs are appropriately prioritized for all requirements/user stories and development tasks;
• Work with the Quality Assurance/Engineering teams to provide user testing and quality assurance on newly developed functionality;
• Assist in the development of internal methodologies and process improvements to increase overall efficiency within the organization;
• Be a champion for understanding and implementing ECS methodologies and best practices at your engagement.

Requirements:
• Must be a U.S. Citizen
• Bachelor's degree
• 5+ years of related Product Management experience, 2+ in professional services/consulting role;
• Experience successfully leading and delivering within Federal consulting engagements
• Clear and concise verbal and written communications;
• Excellent active listening skills;
• Experience in scrum-based Agile development methodology;
• High level of organization and ability to prioritize tasks;
• Ability to develop relationships with client team members at all levels of an organization;
• Ability to informally influence others in a positive way;
• Strong desire to improve and continuously learn;
• Professional demeanor and behavior; can-do attitude;
• Be motivated by serving clients and helping them fulfill their mission;
• Ability to work and manage projects independently and proactively to ‘get things done.';
• Proficiency with MS Office tools, especially Word, Excel, PowerPoint, and Visio, with demonstrated ability to efficiently produce crisp, professional documents;

